    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a concours-level 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in Alpine White. This specimen is powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS system that has been fully overhauled for optimal cam timing. Power is delivered via a 6-speed manual Getrag transmission to a variable M differential lock. Crucially, the rear subframe has been structurally reinforced, and the rod bearings have been replaced with WPC-treated units to ensure long-term mechanical integrity. The suspension retains its factory-spec kinematics with fresh bushings throughout, providing the precise turn-in and lateral stability these chassis are renowned for. Documented service history confirms zero deferred maintenance on this turn-key, investment-grade icon.",
